definition: to keep/to retain/to have reservations (about sth)/to hold back (from saying sth)/to put aside for later
Bulgaria/Bulgarian/abbr. for 保加利亞|保加利亚[Bao3 jia1 li4 ya4]
to defend/to protect/to keep/to guarantee/to ensure/civil administration unit in the baojia 保甲[bao3 jia3] system (old)
to leave (a message etc)/to retain/to stay/to remain/to keep/to preserve

sentences.english: Miss Athill did not keep the letters she received from Mr Field.
sentences.chinese: 阿西爾女士並沒有保留菲爾德先生寫給她的信件。

sentences.english: We reserve the right to claim damages.
sentences.chinese: 我們保留索賠損失的權利。

sentences.english: The four-letter words were always edited out of radio scripts until quite recently.
sentences.chinese: 直到最近廣播稿中的庸俗詞語才讓保留下來。

sentences.english: Office of build Sancha reservations, withdrawal state Department contractor, based Police at the Office.
sentences.chinese: 三岔廳建置保留，撤州判署，設警察分廳。

sentences.english: We'll keep you posted on developments with this one as it nears its release date.
sentences.chinese: 我們將保留您的留言於開發上和接近釋出遊戲時。

sentences.english: The Organisers reserve the right to amend the Schedule of Races should circumstances require.
sentences.chinese: 如有需要，本會將保留修改賽程表之權利。

sentences.english: Objective To probe the nephron spring surgery for renal neoplasms.
sentences.chinese: 目的評估保留腎單位手術治療腎腫瘤的效果。

sentences.english: Shifts the bits of an expression to the right, maintaining sign.
sentences.chinese: 將運算式的位元向右移，保留正負號。

sentences.english: Follow the customs of the new country you are in, or keep your own customs?
sentences.chinese: 入鄉隨俗還是保留自己國家的習俗？

sentences.english: Nolan has reservations about the new diplomas.
sentences.chinese: 諾蘭對新的文憑持保留態度。

sentences.english: Trinity General Insurance Company Limited reserves the final right of approval.
sentences.chinese: 三聯保險有限公司保留保單的最後批覈權。

sentences.english: If You Are The One keeps the typical humor of Feng Xiaogang.
sentences.chinese: 《非誠勿擾》保留了一貫的“馮式幽默”。

sentences.english: They STILL have defacto SLAVE LABOR, in their factories, and on farms.
sentences.chinese: 在工廠和農場裏，他們仍保留有事實上的奴工。

sentences.english: Subrange types maintain the ordinalities of their base types.
sentences.chinese: 子界類型保留了其基類型的序號。

sentences.english: One minus the churn rate is the retention rate .
sentences.chinese: 一減流失率就是保留率。

sentences.english: Some 60% said that saving jobs was more important than paying dividends.
sentences.chinese: 大約60%的人說，保留工作崗位比派發紅利更重要。

definition: to conserve/to preserve/to keep/to save (a file etc) (computing)
to keep/to preserve/extant/to remain (from the past)
to continue to use (old methods)/to apply as before/according to usage
to carry on as before/to follow (an old custom etc)
to hold in storage/to retain/to harbor (feelings)/to entertain (sentiments)/(of abstract things) to exist/there is
